               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; &#xD;
the word mәʿәraf (“chapter”) and the numbers of the chapters;&#xD;
some lines of the incipit page of each Gospels, divided into several groups, alternating with black lines: 7 lines in fol. 10r, 9 lines in fol. 42r, 8 lines in fol. 62r, 8 lines in fol. 96r;&#xD;
the incipit (2-3 lines) of all the chapters; &#xD;
some paragraph beginnings;&#xD;
parts of Canon tables;&#xD;
the stichometry for the Gospel of Matthew (fol. 40ra, l.20);&#xD;
some extras notes at the top of the leaves;&#xD;
Ethiopic numbers indicating the “Tituli” (s. esp. in fol. 40v, ls. 1, 2);&#xD;
elements of the punctuation signs.</rubric>
